<meta name="assert" content="Grid placement algorithm is able to select the right line when defined implicitly with grid-template-areas."><meta name="assert" content="Grid placement algorithm is able to select the right line when defined implicitly with grid-template-areas.">
<style><meta content="Grid placement algorithm is able to select the right line when defined implicitly with grid-template-areas.">
.grid {
  display: grid;
  width: 300px;
  height: 300px;
  grid-template-areas: "area";
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, 100px);
  grid-template-rows: repeat(auto-fill, 100px) [area-end] 100px;
}
.grid > div {
  grid-area: area;
  background: green;
}
</style>
<div></div>Test passes if there is a filled green square.xht">
<meta name="assert" content="Grid placement algorithm is able to select the right line when defined implicitly with grid-template-areas.">
<style>
.grid {
  display: grid;
  width: 300px;
  height: 300px;
  grid-template-areas: "area";
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, 100px);
  grid-template-rows: repeat(auto-fill, 100px) [area-end] 100px;
}
.grid > div {
  grid-area: area;
  background: green;
}
</style>
<p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>
